args: Ewww... Carrots and peppers are gross.
You can have mine, Emilia! Eat them\njust like always, 'kay? Pleeeease?
I'm sorry, Anna, but you're going to\nhave to eat those by yourself.
I only hate bad little girls who won't eat\ntheir veggies. Are you one of those?
What?! N-no! Please don't hate me!
Then let's see you gobble up all those\nveggies. Because if you don't...
O-okay, I'll eat 'em! I'll eat 'em right now!
(I feel like a monster for threatening you,\nAnna, but it's the only way you'll learn.)
I... *sniffle* I hate carrots and peppers.\n*nibble* Blech.
(You've got this—and I think I've\ngot this as well.)
Emilia, heeelp! It hurts too bad to walk...
Aww, it looks like you skinned your knee\nthere, kiddo. But you're okay—a little\nscrape like that won't stop you.
No, I really can't walk! It huuuurts!
You really can't? Even though you're\nthe strongest little girl I know?
Much more than you know, Anna.
Even if you don't believe it yet, I do.
I do. Now up we go! Get back on those\nbig strong legs all by yourself!
Look at that! You did it all on your own!\nNow do you believe me when I say\nyou're super strong?
Hee hee! I guess I AM pretty strong...
Stern in one moment and nurturing the next,\nMelsa fostered Anna's independence—\nand in time, her efforts bore fruit...
Emilia! Mom! I'm gonna go play\nwith my friends outside!
Ha ha! I fell! What a doof.
But it's okay! I'm super strong!
I think she might finally be ready\nto leave her sister's side.
I think so, too. Thank you so much, Melsa.
Now BOTH of us are ready to move on,\nas a family.
And I hope...I hope Emilia can rest easy\nknowing she has no unfinished business\nto worry about.
...Oh, that reminds me. Melsa: I was\nwondering if you'd want to visit her grave.\nI think she'd really like to meet you.
Of course. But first, I need to return her\nname so I can meet her as my own self.
And that means telling Anna the truth.
Um, so what'd you wanna talk about\nall the way out here, Emilia?
Anna, sweetie... I'm not your big sister.
My name is Melsa. Not Emilia.
Mel...sa? But you're STILL Emilia, right?
Because you're a zombie. You came back\nto life and you're my sister.
I'm only dressed up as a zombie, honey.\nIt's just pretend—not real.
Emilia is sleeping in her grave.\nShe has been ever since she died.
No... No! I don't want that! It's so lonely\nwhen she's gone! I miss her so... *sniff*
Don't cry, Anna. You're strong, remember?
No buts. You can eat all your veggies,\nyou can walk off a skinned knee, and you\ncan go play with friends all by yourself.
That's how strong you are—and that's why\nyou'll be all right even if your big sister\nisn't there to help you.
You're going to get through life just fine,\nbecause that's what strong girls do.
Even if I'm all by myself?!
You've got this! Up on your feet, Anna!\nYou can do this on your own!
(Melsa's not my sister for real,\nbut she's cheering me on like she is.)
(She said nice things to me like Emilia\nalways did, and it made me really happy.)
(So I want to try to be like she says.\nI wanna do things on my own.)
Okay. I'll try. Even if I'm on my own,\nI'll still try really hard.
And you're going to do GREAT, Anna,\nbecause I know how strong you are.
Hee hee! Thanks, Melsa. Hearing that\nfrom you makes me feel way better.
I'll be okay as long as you're with me!
Sweetie, I'm sorry, but... I can't do that.\nI have my own family back at the Halidom\nthat I have to return to.
Oh. Right. If you're not really my sister,\nthen I guess you can't stay.
*sniff* It's gonna be lonely on my own...
But I'm not gonna cry, because I'm strong!
You really are, Anna. And though we only\ngot a little while together, I'm very proud\nto have been your big sis.
I'm glad I got to be with you, too.
I have one last lesson for you, Anna:\nthe perfect words for times like these.
(Right, Sarisse? When you have to part\nwith people you love, it's not goodbye.)
There's no rule that says we can never\nmeet again, so you can come play at the\nHalidom whenever you like!
Yaaaaaay! I'm totally gonna do that!
